Did you know you can use essential oils to help naturally balance your hormones?⁠
⁠
Here are a few of the essential oils I recommend friends and family use ⬇️⁠
⁠
Clary sage’s biggest benefit is that it helps balance estrogen in the body. If you have infertility or estrogen-induced cancer, clary sage helps balance your estrogen levels and hormones. ⁠
⁠
Thyme oil benefits the body by producing more progesterone, which helps balance the body’s hormones. ⁠
⁠
And, sandalwood oil helps balance testosterone levels in both men and women. ⁠
⁠
Want to learn more ways to naturally balance your hormones? Head over to my stories and swipe up.

Water is vital for overall health and should be your No. 1 beverage choice; however, your body needs electrolytes for proper hydration. ⁠
⁠
These seven foods are high in electrolytes and will help your body stay hydrated! ⁠
⁠
One way I like to incorporate these foods into my diet is with a smoothie made with greens, fruit and coconut milk or with a big salad of mixed greens topped with chopped veggies, avocado and a protein. ⁠

Need an extra dose of superfoods and an easy dinner recipe? ⁠
⁠
This salmon and kale salad might be exactly what you’re looking for! It’s bursting with not only flavor but tons of nutrients as well.⁠
⁠
You'll get vitamins B12, D and omega-3 fatty acids from the salmon, and vitamins K, A, C and more from the kale. ⁠
⁠
What you'll need ⬇️⁠
Salmon:⁠
4 salmon fillets, wild-caught⁠
salt and pepper⁠
1 tablespoon grapeseed oil⁠
2 teaspoons lemon juice⁠
⁠
Dressing:⁠
1/4 cup German or Dijon mustard, preferably with an apple cider vinegar base (as opposed to distilled white vinegar)⁠
3 tablespoons raw, local honey⁠
2 tablespoons goat’s milk yogurt or soaked raw cashews⁠
1 teaspoon chipotle powder⁠
½ teaspoon garlic powder⁠
dash of salt⁠
⁠
Salad:⁠
12 ounces baby kale⁠
3 green onions, chopped⁠
1 red pepper, chopped⁠
⁠
For the full recipe and to learn more about the superfoods used head to my profile and click the link in my bio. ⁠
⁠

Adding a few servings of superfoods to your diet can be simple and delicious. I like adding a variety of superfoods to my morning smoothies, but you can also use them in salads, power bites, and even soups. ⁠
⁠

When our immune system is working properly we hardly notice it. ⁠
⁠
But when we have an under-or over-active immune system, we are at a greater risk of developing infections and other conditions. ⁠
⁠
The good news is there are herbs and supplements we can take to help boost our immune health. ⁠
⁠
For example, elderberry can help fight colds, the flu, allergies and inflammation! And zinc can help reduce cold-related symptoms and even shorten colds. ⁠
⁠
Want to learn how to use these immune boosters? Follow the link in my bio.⁠
⁠
#immunesystem #immuneresponse #immunityboosting #coldandfluseason #boostyourimmunity #immunitysupport

It shouldn't be a secret that diet plays a major role in immune health.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Besides adding foods and supplements into your routine, adding a few immune–supporting drinks to your daily diet may also be beneficial.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
⁠Here are two of my favorite, simple immune-supporting drinks. Get the recipes below!⁣⁠⁠
⁣⁠⁠
🍋 Immune Boosting Shot:⁣⁠⁠
Using a juicer, add one lemon and 1-2 inch knobs of ginger. Top juice with a dash of cayenne, and enjoy! If you don't have a juicer, use a blender and strain the solids for a juice.⁣⁠⁠
⁣⁠⁠
🍓 Immune Boosting Smoothie:⁣⁠⁠
In a blender, add 1/2 grapefruit, 1/2 cup fresh or frozen strawberries, 2 to 4 oz of sheep or goat yogurt (coconut yogurt also works), 1-2 tsp grated ginger, 1 tbsp local raw honey and coconut milk or water for your preferred texture. Pulse until well blended and enjoy!⁣⁠⁠
⁣⁠⁠
For even more information on how you can boost your immune system, including my top recommendations for herbs, food, supplements and lifestyle changes, follow the link in my bio!⁠⁠
⁠⁠

⁠
